result.execSummary:
The defendant Morris Moore was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Sex Offender Registry - Fail to Satisfy Registration Requirements AMENDED - w/out Repeater enhancer, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 301.45(3)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Defendant has 175 days CFTS on this case.

miscConds.notes:
Defendant must pay court cost, the DNA surcharge and the cost of supervision during supervision.
If supervision is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered against the defendant and in favor of restitution victims and governmental entities for the balance due.  Collections may include income assignment.

Defendant is to engage in programming to obtain employment skills.
Defendant must obtain and maintain employment as he is able.

Defendant must complete a mental health assessment and follow through with any treatment that is recommended.
Defendant must complete a Cognative Intervention Program.

Defendant must obey all rules and regulations while on supervision.
Firearms warning given.
Appeal rights given.
Voting is prohibited until sentence is complete and civil rights have been restored.
Defendant must be in compliance with the requirements of the Sex Offender Registry.
ABSOLUTE SOBRIETY - no alcohol or controlled substances.  Defendant may take medications as prescribed by a physician.
Defendant is to be held until October 22, 2014 so the Department of Corrections can work with him and acquire temporary housing.  
DEFENDANT MUST NOT BE RELEASED IN THE MIDDLE OF THE NIGHT.
